"{\"_values\": {\"num\": 53, \"title\": \"\\u2018Today History Was Made\\u2019: Derek Chauvin Found Guilty Of Murder In George Floyd\\u2019s Death\", \"url\": \"https://www.forbes.com/sites/jemimamcevoy/2021/04/20/derek-chauvin-found-guilty-of-murder-in-george-floyds-death/\", \"description\": \"The former Minneapolis Police officer was found guilty on all three counts. \", \"author\": \"Jemima McEvoy\", \"content\": [\"Former Minneapolis Police Officer Derek Chauvin was found guilty of two counts of murder and manslaughter Tuesday in the death of George Floyd, who Chauvin pinned to the ground with his knee on the Black man's neck for more than nine minutes last summer.\\u00a0\", \"\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdToday history was made,\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd Floyd\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds family attorney Benjamin Crump said after the verdict. \\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdWe are finally as a country starting to live up to the promise of equal justice under the law for all people ... It was sacrificial blood that made this moment possible for the history of America.\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd \", \"During the weeks-long trial, watched by\", \" across the U.S., prosecutors argued the arrest had unfolded exactly as it appeared in the video captured by a teenage bystander that initially drew the nation\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds attention to the case. The state called in a litany of police use-of-force experts and medical professionals to testify that Chauvin acted unnecessarily when he used his knee to pin Floyd to the ground for more than nine minutes over a counterfeit $20 bill, and that his actions ultimately killed Floyd due to oxygen deprivation. \\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdUse your common sense. Believe your eyes. What you saw, you saw,\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd prosecutor Steve Schleicher said in closing arguments. Meanwhile, Chauvin\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds defense attorney Eric Nelson appealed to jurors that the case was more complicated than the footage let on, highlighting the minutes leading up to the arrest. Nelson argued Chauvin followed his training in the midst of a \\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffddynamic\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd and \\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdfluid\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffd situation involving a large man struggling with three officers, and that Floyd instead died of other factors, including drugs and underlying conditions. Witnesses testified in support of both arguments, but the medical examiner who performed Floyd\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds autopsy testified that it was ultimately the police restraint that overwhelmed Floyd\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds already overburdened heart.\", \"Minneapolis, and other major cities, are anticipating a strong reaction to the trial\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds outcome. Floyd\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds death sparked months of racial justice protests and a global movement that led to changes in many of the U.S.\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds biggest police departments. Unrest has recently resurfaced over the deaths of two Black young men in police custody: 20-year-old Daunte Wright and 13-year-old Adam Toledo.\\u00a0\", \"The other three officers involved in Floyd\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffds arrest\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdTou Thao, Thomas Lane and J. Alexander Kueng\\ufffd\\ufffd\\ufffdare scheduled to stand trial together in August. They face charges of aiding and abetting second-degree manslaughter and second degree murder.\", \" (Forbes)\"]}}"